body:
So, with all the new Shadow Isles stories we now know that such a dreadful and grim place wasn&#039;t always like that.

Before balance was broken by the ruined king&#039;s sorcery, they were the Blessed Isles.

So... how come Bard didn&#039;t intervene? {{champion:432}}

replies.body:
Thanks so much for your answer and for reminding me of the Wonder Above teaser! 

So this suggests that Bard can intervene without being seen. Still brings some other questions though, when and why does Bard decide to reveal itself instead of remaining unseen? 

His entire concept is amazing, I'm hoping we'll get to hear more of him in the future lore. {{champion:432}}

Well let's see what resulted from option 2.

{{champion:82}} 

Oh good job Bard, you just allowed Valoran's former God-King to resurrect.

{{champion:83}} {{champion:120}} {{champion:30}} {{champion:412}} {{champion:429}} 

And these guys came out as well.

Why don't you go back to farming your chimes and troll someone else, you fat tub of lard?
